The paper discusses a decentralized market-based approach for supply chain formation, which involves multiple agents and resource allocation. This topic falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of auctions and bidding policies, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of resource allocation, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC).
